    "updated_at": "2015-02-28T00:01:25Z",
    "body": "> In addition, when I get the bounds of a maximized window, the position returned is negative ([-8, -8]).  For any logic that tries to bound these coordinates within the display area, this will be error-prone.\n\nThis is unfortunately an expected behavior on Windows, see:\nhttp://blogs.msdn.com/b/oldnewthing/archive/2012/03/26/10287385.aspx\n\nTo work around this you should treat maximized window specially in your logic.\n"
